<refnamediv><refname>imnormalize</refname><refpurpose>Normalize image values to a target range.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imnormalize(im)
out = imnormalize(im, alpha, beta)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>im</term><listitem><para>Input image or numeric array.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>alpha</term><listitem><para>Lower output value. Default is <literal>0</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>beta</term><listitem><para>Upper output value. Default is <literal>1</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Double image normalized channel-by-channel to <literal>[alpha, beta]</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imnormalize</function> scales each channel independently to <literal>[alpha, beta]</literal>.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
im = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/" + "baboon.png"));
out = imnormalize(im);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
